snippet.textDisplay:
I don't like what they did with the body. The hood's too short anf and they de-emphasized the hood fenders. The 0-60 time is ridiculously fast, but it only really matters if you take it to track days. Driving a sports car is about the fun factor. I'm sorry, but just bracing yourself and stomping down on the gas ISN'T fun. Fun is maneuvering the car around curves at speed...using a manual transmission so you can really feel the road.

Unless you're disabled (like a war vet missing a leg),then an automatic Corvette is heresy. It's SACRILEGE!
